<div id="Wayang-Kulit-About" class="tabcontent">

	<div>	
		<p>The art of Wayang Kulit is a traditional form of puppet-shadow play originating from Java and Bali in Indonesia. It is a living art form that reflects the history, values, beliefs, and creativity of the Indonesian people. However, it is facing challenges and threats in the modern world, such as the declining interest of the younger generation and the dwindling number of skilled dalangs and puppet makers.</p>
		<img src="C:\Users\Reign\Downloads\386873171_274927768775066_4321880382055602366_n.png" alt="wayang kulit" style="width:100%">
	</div>

	<div>
		<p>To preserve Wayang Kulit, we must raise awareness and appreciation for this art form among the public, especially the youth. We must also support and promote the dalangs and puppet makers who dedicate their lives to this art form. By doing so, we can keep Wayang Kulit alive and relevant for present and future generations.</p>
	</div>

	<div>
		<p>One way to achieve these goals is by creating and performing our own Wayang Kulit shadow puppet play. We, a group of students passionate about Wayang Kulit, have practiced hard and are ready to showcase our work to the world. Our puppet show is based on the classic piece, "The Story of The Ramayana."</p>
	</div>

</div>



